1
00:00:00,480 --> 00:00:01,080
(Previously)
Arnold.

2
00:00:01,081 --> 00:00:03,639
I think I need time to think it through.

3
00:00:03,640 --> 00:00:07,280
I'll also do my best to win you back.

4
00:00:07,920 --> 00:00:11,640
Rome, I'm sorry
for hurting you again and again.

5
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:14,640
From now on, I'll be the one chasing you.

6
00:00:16,120 --> 00:00:17,960
I think I'm too naïve

7
00:00:18,080 --> 00:00:20,680
to let Romeo and Romeo end up together.

8
00:00:21,280 --> 00:00:24,720
Actually, tearing them apart by death
is the best solution.

9
00:00:25,800 --> 00:00:26,800
What's up, Timmy?

10
00:00:29,240 --> 00:00:29,760
Jack.

11
00:00:30,200 --> 00:00:30,960
What happened?

12
00:00:31,120 --> 00:00:32,800
The ride Timmy took home was in a crash.

13
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:34,040
It's my fault.

14
00:00:34,120 --> 00:00:34,960
It's okay.

15
00:00:35,120 --> 00:00:36,120
I'm right here.

16
00:00:40,500 --> 00:00:42,700
(Episode 11: Off Stage)

17
00:00:58,800 --> 00:01:00,280
Mr. Tananop's relative?

18
00:01:00,400 --> 00:01:00,800
Yes.

19
00:01:00,801 --> 00:01:02,480
He's been treated. You can go in now.

20
00:01:07,920 --> 00:01:09,480
Timmy, how are you?

21
00:01:12,640 --> 00:01:13,800
Just a broken arm, Jack.

22
00:01:14,640 --> 00:01:16,320
Lucky me, I didn't hit my head.

23
00:01:27,840 --> 00:01:28,960
I'm not dead yet, Tua.

24
00:01:29,560 --> 00:01:31,000
Don't give me that look.

25
00:01:33,080 --> 00:01:34,680
Is this really the time to joke, Timmy?

26
00:01:35,840 --> 00:01:37,000
Everyone's been worried sick.

27
00:01:38,160 --> 00:01:39,800
You're lucky you made it, Timmy.

28
00:01:40,320 --> 00:01:42,240
It was a car crash.
Don't act like it's nothing.

29
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:47,000
You know,

30
00:01:48,040 --> 00:01:52,160
when my bike got hit, I saw my parents…

31
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:55,960
and you guys too.

32
00:01:59,040 --> 00:02:02,040
Timmy, don't say that.

33
00:02:02,480 --> 00:02:04,840
I was like, “Damn it.

34
00:02:05,840 --> 00:02:11,680
Do I really have to die right after
my last, super dramatic project?”

35
00:02:21,480 --> 00:02:23,240
We're all friends. Don't forget that.

36
00:02:26,520 --> 00:02:28,440
Just get some rest. Stop talking.

37
00:02:30,760 --> 00:02:32,800
Fine, I'll shut up.

38
00:02:35,200 --> 00:02:36,720
You guys should patch things up.

39
00:02:39,480 --> 00:02:43,440
Let my near-death experience
count for something.

40
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,640
Go on. Talk it out.

41
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:53,240
I'm going to sleep.

42
00:04:21,500 --> 00:04:25,000
"Only Friends : Dream On"

43
00:04:42,560 --> 00:04:44,200
Why is it just the two of you today?

44
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:47,000
Where's Tua?

45
00:04:47,040 --> 00:04:49,640
He said he had to help out
at his family's amusement park.

46
00:04:49,920 --> 00:04:50,920
He might be here later.

47
00:04:51,520 --> 00:04:53,200
You guys haven't talked to him?

48
00:04:54,320 --> 00:04:56,200
Are you waiting for me to die first?

49
00:04:56,640 --> 00:04:58,240
Timmy, what are you saying?

50
00:04:59,200 --> 00:05:02,800
So who's going to
thank the sponsor in my place?

51
00:05:04,720 --> 00:05:05,720
I am.

52
00:05:05,960 --> 00:05:07,480
And you're going empty-handed?

53
00:05:08,280 --> 00:05:10,400
You're not even getting a gift?

54
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:12,600
Do I have to?

55
00:05:13,080 --> 00:05:14,080
You absolutely do.

56
00:05:17,040 --> 00:05:22,440
Today, you and Dean are going to
buy a gift and deliver it to our sponsor.

57
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:24,800
The producer's in the hospital,

58
00:05:24,960 --> 00:05:29,200
so the director and the lead
have to do it instead.

59
00:05:29,720 --> 00:05:30,720
It's only right.

60
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:34,680
Seriously, you guys.

61
00:05:50,080 --> 00:05:51,520
Wow.

62
00:05:52,240 --> 00:05:53,760
You brought your personal assistant?

63
00:05:58,080 --> 00:05:59,480
I've thought it through.

64
00:05:59,960 --> 00:06:01,400
I want to play hard to get for once.

65
00:06:05,040 --> 00:06:07,880
He messed up.
He'll have to work hard to redeem himself.

66
00:06:08,800 --> 00:06:11,680
Should I have the staff
lock Arnold in the haunted house?

67
00:06:13,080 --> 00:06:15,280
We can let him out tomorrow.

68
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:20,880
Are we done with the costumes?

69
00:06:21,480 --> 00:06:21,960
Yeah, we are.

70
00:06:21,961 --> 00:06:23,120
Then let's go.

71
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:25,000
Come on.

72
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:32,560
If you mess up big, you go big to fix it.

73
00:06:35,040 --> 00:06:36,040
Thank you, sir.

74
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:52,480
Are you tired?

75
00:06:53,760 --> 00:06:54,760
No.

76
00:06:55,080 --> 00:06:57,160
There's actually nothing else to do today.

77
00:06:58,200 --> 00:06:59,200
You're free to go.

78
00:06:59,960 --> 00:07:00,960
That's okay.

79
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:05,000
I'll stay till the end and
take you home after.

80
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:08,880
I'm not sure yet.

81
00:07:09,280 --> 00:07:10,720
I might stay over at my dad's.

82
00:07:12,720 --> 00:07:13,720
Okay.

83
00:07:14,280 --> 00:07:15,280
Oh, hey.

84
00:07:17,640 --> 00:07:18,640
About the swing dance…

85
00:07:20,320 --> 00:07:21,400
Do you still want to do it?

86
00:07:21,880 --> 00:07:24,720
I heard there's a
Swing Night coming up.

87
00:07:26,160 --> 00:07:27,160
Want to go with me?

88
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:32,400
I'm planning to go…

89
00:07:33,400 --> 00:07:36,160
and find a new dance partner there.

90
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:44,640
No one matches your rhythm like I do, Tua.

91
00:07:45,960 --> 00:07:46,960
Trust me.

92
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:51,720
We'll see about that.

93
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:07,120
Did you say go big, sir?

94
00:08:08,640 --> 00:08:09,640
Alright then.

95
00:08:53,880 --> 00:08:55,160
Why didn't you pick up my calls?

96
00:08:57,320 --> 00:08:58,320
I'm busy.

97
00:09:00,920 --> 00:09:03,320
I'm working. I need to focus.

98
00:09:06,120 --> 00:09:07,120
Why are you here?

99
00:09:09,920 --> 00:09:12,880
I just came to ask
about the playlist you made for me.

100
00:09:13,920 --> 00:09:14,920
Where did it go?

101
00:09:17,680 --> 00:09:18,920
It was always my playlist.

102
00:09:19,800 --> 00:09:20,800
It was never yours.

103
00:09:22,720 --> 00:09:25,520
And I don't like it
anymore, so I deleted it.

104
00:09:26,040 --> 00:09:27,040
That's it.

105
00:09:29,960 --> 00:09:31,800
You didn't like it
anymore, so you deleted it?

106
00:09:32,600 --> 00:09:33,000
Mm.

107
00:09:33,320 --> 00:09:34,320
What about me?

108
00:09:36,560 --> 00:09:37,560
I'm not into it anymore.

109
00:09:38,880 --> 00:09:42,760
Sorry. Go find someone else's playlists.

110
00:09:54,480 --> 00:09:55,480
Are you free today?

111
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:57,560
Let's grab something to eat after work.

112
00:09:58,680 --> 00:09:59,680
I'm busy.

113
00:10:01,240 --> 00:10:02,240
Doing what?

114
00:10:02,680 --> 00:10:04,120
I don't know. I'm just busy.

115
00:10:04,680 --> 00:10:06,080
And I don't know when I'll be free.

116
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:10,600
Fine.

117
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:14,240
It's fine if you don't
know when you'll be free.

118
00:10:14,760 --> 00:10:15,760
I'm free.

119
00:10:18,680 --> 00:10:21,240
I'll just hang around here…

120
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:23,200
until you are.

121
00:10:23,400 --> 00:10:24,400
Until you are.

122
00:10:51,080 --> 00:10:52,080
Here's a gift for you.

123
00:10:53,240 --> 00:10:55,680
Thank you so much for sponsoring our play.

124
00:10:56,480 --> 00:10:58,640
Timmy asked me to apologize
for not coming in person.

125
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:00,840
Oh, it's totally fine.

126
00:11:01,360 --> 00:11:02,640
Come on. Have a seat.

127
00:11:05,280 --> 00:11:08,480
Your play was a huge success.

128
00:11:08,880 --> 00:11:12,120
Even my boss said I
picked the right project.

129
00:11:12,800 --> 00:11:13,480
Thank you.

130
00:11:13,800 --> 00:11:16,640
Good thing I trusted
the buzz around the ArnoldDean ship.

131
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:20,320
My product's engagement
is skyrocketing right now.

132
00:11:22,320 --> 00:11:25,640
That ship really saved the play.

133
00:11:28,360 --> 00:11:29,360
Thank you, ma'am.

134
00:11:29,640 --> 00:11:34,760
But I think the play was a hit
because of our director's skill.

135
00:11:36,400 --> 00:11:37,400
That's true.

136
00:11:38,240 --> 00:11:40,760
Jack, you're amazing.

137
00:11:41,560 --> 00:11:43,280
I watched the play and loved it.

138
00:11:45,080 --> 00:11:49,480
You adapted it in a way that
perfectly resonates with this generation.

139
00:11:49,920 --> 00:11:54,480
People who love each other
should end up together,

140
00:11:55,080 --> 00:11:56,080
right?

141
00:12:13,320 --> 00:12:14,560
Where are you going after this?

142
00:12:20,960 --> 00:12:22,360
I think I'll head back to my place.

143
00:12:30,920 --> 00:12:32,120
Want to grab something to eat?

144
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:43,000
I'll pass.

145
00:12:46,880 --> 00:12:47,880
I'm heading out.

146
00:12:50,360 --> 00:12:51,360
Mm.

147
00:13:38,080 --> 00:13:40,080
Hello, everyone!

148
00:13:48,760 --> 00:13:49,760
Tua.

149
00:13:51,040 --> 00:13:52,040
I was wrong.

150
00:13:52,400 --> 00:13:53,400
Please forgive me.

151
00:13:55,560 --> 00:13:56,560
Please.

152
00:14:01,546 --> 00:14:03,775
Arnold, what are you doing?

153
00:14:10,160 --> 00:14:11,160
I messed up.

154
00:14:11,560 --> 00:14:12,560
I'm sorry.

155
00:14:12,800 --> 00:14:14,160
I won't hurt you again.

156
00:14:14,600 --> 00:14:18,440
If I do, may I be
reborn as this dog in my next life.

157
00:14:18,960 --> 00:14:20,560
Woof woof.

158
00:14:24,640 --> 00:14:26,000
The dog did nothing wrong.

159
00:14:26,520 --> 00:14:27,600
Don't drag it into this.

160
00:14:29,880 --> 00:14:30,880
Woof.

161
00:14:31,080 --> 00:14:32,960
Are you two boyfriends?

162
00:14:34,480 --> 00:14:36,240
Yes, we are.

163
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:39,640
So you did something wrong,
and you're trying to make it up to him?

164
00:14:39,800 --> 00:14:40,560
That's right.

165
00:14:40,800 --> 00:14:43,719
But no matter what I
do, he won't forgive me.

166
00:14:43,720 --> 00:14:44,400
What should I do?

167
00:14:44,520 --> 00:14:48,240
Wow, you dressed up just for him.
If I were you, I'd fold.

168
00:14:48,720 --> 00:14:52,600
I got all dressed up for him.
He should soften and forgive me, right?

169
00:14:52,920 --> 00:14:53,560
Right, everyone?

170
00:14:53,640 --> 00:14:55,200
Yes!

171
00:14:55,680 --> 00:14:56,480
Forgive.

172
00:14:56,520 --> 00:14:57,520
Forgive.

173
00:14:57,560 --> 00:14:58,560
Forgive.

174
00:14:58,840 --> 00:14:59,840
Forgive.

175
00:14:59,920 --> 00:15:00,920
Forgive.

176
00:15:01,040 --> 00:15:01,800
Forgive.

177
00:15:02,040 --> 00:15:03,040
Forgive.

178
00:15:03,520 --> 00:15:05,160
Forgive.

179
00:15:05,240 --> 00:15:05,920
Forgive.
Well?

180
00:15:08,320 --> 00:15:09,520
Are you going to forgive me?

181
00:15:27,240 --> 00:15:28,240
Mm.

182
00:15:28,280 --> 00:15:30,080
Whoo!

183
00:15:37,560 --> 00:15:38,640
Hey. Are you okay?

184
00:15:40,440 --> 00:15:42,600
I am. I just landed awkwardly.

185
00:15:44,960 --> 00:15:47,280
But I'm good. He forgave me!

186
00:15:47,760 --> 00:15:48,760
Yay!

187
00:16:04,040 --> 00:16:06,040
So you're just going to follow me around?

188
00:16:06,680 --> 00:16:07,880
Don't you have anything to do?

189
00:16:09,240 --> 00:16:11,040
I'm just doing what
you did to me back then.

190
00:16:11,800 --> 00:16:13,000
Now do you get how I felt?

191
00:16:17,840 --> 00:16:19,760
Do whatever you want. I don't care.

192
00:16:22,040 --> 00:16:25,080
You wouldn't talk to me,
so I'll just follow you everywhere.

193
00:16:32,400 --> 00:16:33,400
You want to talk?

194
00:16:34,920 --> 00:16:35,360
Yes.

195
00:16:35,600 --> 00:16:36,600
Prove it.

196
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:41,600
How?

197
00:16:43,040 --> 00:16:44,640
There. An ice bath.

198
00:16:46,600 --> 00:16:49,600
If you can stay in there for two minutes,
I'll talk to you.

199
00:16:53,240 --> 00:16:54,320
No way, it's freezing.

200
00:16:55,200 --> 00:16:56,200
See?

201
00:16:56,400 --> 00:16:58,560
You don't like me enough to go that far.

202
00:17:01,600 --> 00:17:02,600
Wait.

203
00:17:03,120 --> 00:17:04,120
Just two minutes, right?

204
00:17:12,760 --> 00:17:17,440
If I do it, you have to keep your word.

205
00:17:19,680 --> 00:17:22,440
Sure. I'm a man of my word.

206
00:17:44,640 --> 00:17:46,880
Calling it now, he won't last a minute.

207
00:18:28,040 --> 00:18:28,520
Whoa.

208
00:18:28,920 --> 00:18:29,920
He's quite a fighter.

209
00:18:54,840 --> 00:18:56,200
Cut. We got it.

210
00:18:57,360 --> 00:18:58,360
We passed?

211
00:18:59,480 --> 00:19:00,480
Thank you.

212
00:19:00,920 --> 00:19:01,920
Want to take a look?

213
00:19:02,120 --> 00:19:03,120
Let's see.

214
00:19:04,680 --> 00:19:05,920
Is it good? Is it okay?

215
00:19:06,280 --> 00:19:07,280
It is.

216
00:19:07,400 --> 00:19:09,560
The love in your eyes
shines through your glasses.

217
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:14,159
Of course. If we love each other,
we have to show it.

218
00:19:14,160 --> 00:19:15,160
Isn't that right, Mew?

219
00:19:16,400 --> 00:19:18,200
Top, stop. You're embarrassing me.

220
00:19:21,080 --> 00:19:22,959
The delivery's here.
I'll go get the coffee.

221
00:19:22,960 --> 00:19:23,960
Yeah.

222
00:19:32,880 --> 00:19:33,880
Whoa, Jack.

223
00:19:34,960 --> 00:19:36,560
Is my job stressing you out that much?

224
00:19:36,640 --> 00:19:37,920
You're drinking already.

225
00:19:40,320 --> 00:19:42,480
No. I just felt like it.

226
00:19:48,393 --> 00:19:50,073
Hey, where's Dean?

227
00:19:50,880 --> 00:19:51,880
I haven't seen him today.

228
00:19:59,680 --> 00:20:00,680
I don't know.

229
00:20:01,280 --> 00:20:02,720
We broke up, so I don't care.

230
00:20:04,800 --> 00:20:07,160
Hey, I'm sorry.

231
00:20:07,920 --> 00:20:09,000
Didn't mean to bring it up.

232
00:20:09,160 --> 00:20:10,160
It's all good.

233
00:20:18,680 --> 00:20:19,840
Do you want to talk about it?

234
00:20:20,920 --> 00:20:23,440
Or do you want to talk to Top?

235
00:20:27,640 --> 00:20:28,880
Mew, can I ask you something?

236
00:20:31,800 --> 00:20:33,400
Why did you give Top a chance back then?

237
00:20:43,520 --> 00:20:44,640
Back then?

238
00:20:47,400 --> 00:20:49,480
I think… it was love.

239
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:54,600
And Top made it clear he was truly sorry.

240
00:20:55,560 --> 00:20:57,120
He tried hard to change.

241
00:20:59,080 --> 00:21:04,560
I guess it was his sincerity
that brought me back to him.

242
00:21:11,560 --> 00:21:12,720
Do you still trust him?

243
00:21:15,560 --> 00:21:16,560
I do.

244
00:21:17,240 --> 00:21:18,240
Of course I do.

245
00:21:19,960 --> 00:21:24,640
If people in a relationship don't trust
each other, there's no way they'll be happy.

246
00:21:25,920 --> 00:21:27,320
Then why stay together?

247
00:21:42,560 --> 00:21:43,560
Jack.

248
00:21:45,400 --> 00:21:48,120
I don't know how badly Dean messed up.

249
00:21:50,880 --> 00:21:52,640
Only you can decide

250
00:21:54,840 --> 00:21:56,800
if you love him enough
to give him another chance.

251
00:22:07,720 --> 00:22:08,840
Here comes the coffee.

252
00:22:12,520 --> 00:22:13,520
Thank you.

253
00:22:14,880 --> 00:22:15,640
Less sweet?

254
00:22:15,880 --> 00:22:16,880
Yeah, less sweet.

255
00:22:20,360 --> 00:22:21,360
Well?

256
00:22:21,800 --> 00:22:22,400
Sweet.

257
00:22:22,640 --> 00:22:23,640
The coffee?

258
00:22:23,680 --> 00:22:24,680
You.

259
00:22:25,280 --> 00:22:26,480
Look at how cute you are.

260
00:22:27,800 --> 00:22:28,720
But we were pretty sweet just now.
Oh?

261
00:22:29,400 --> 00:22:29,720
Yes.

262
00:22:29,880 --> 00:22:31,160
What were you two talking about?

263
00:22:54,000 --> 00:22:55,000
How's your friend?

264
00:22:55,040 --> 00:22:56,040
Is he recovering well?

265
00:22:57,453 --> 00:23:00,412
He is. He's safe now.

266
00:23:03,640 --> 00:23:04,640
I'm not though.

267
00:23:07,320 --> 00:23:10,400
Did you and Jack
really end things on good terms?

268
00:23:14,320 --> 00:23:16,120
As good as it could be.

269
00:23:18,800 --> 00:23:21,080
What happens next is up to Jack.

270
00:23:22,920 --> 00:23:23,960
There's not much I can do.

271
00:23:28,320 --> 00:23:29,800
If there's nothing you can do,

272
00:23:31,000 --> 00:23:33,080
why not open your heart to someone new?

273
00:23:46,640 --> 00:23:48,000
Can I take care of you?

274
00:23:50,200 --> 00:23:51,200
I'm ready.

275
00:23:53,280 --> 00:23:56,320
I can accept every part of you, unlike him.

276
00:23:59,480 --> 00:24:00,960
Will you give me a chance?

277
00:24:31,200 --> 00:24:32,200
I'm sorry.

278
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:40,040
Even if Jack and I can't get back together…

279
00:24:44,680 --> 00:24:45,920
you're not the one for me.

280
00:25:05,080 --> 00:25:06,200
Are you sure, Dean?

281
00:25:09,719 --> 00:25:10,719
Because from now on,

282
00:25:12,840 --> 00:25:14,120
I'm really letting you go.

283
00:25:26,760 --> 00:25:31,880
Thank you for everything
you've done for me.

284
00:25:33,500 --> 00:25:37,860
But I think it's better for both of us

285
00:25:41,200 --> 00:25:43,240
if I stay true to my feelings.

286
00:26:16,000 --> 00:26:17,000
You're finally here.

287
00:26:17,480 --> 00:26:17,960
Pete.

288
00:26:18,091 --> 00:26:19,400
Why so late?

289
00:26:19,720 --> 00:26:20,960
I thought you weren't coming.

290
00:26:22,440 --> 00:26:23,440
Are you drunk?

291
00:26:23,480 --> 00:26:24,480
A little.

292
00:26:26,818 --> 00:26:27,813
Where are your friends?

293
00:26:28,120 --> 00:26:30,640
Not with me. I'm alone tonight.

294
00:26:31,032 --> 00:26:32,792
I wanted to see you DJ.

295
00:26:33,520 --> 00:26:34,960
I like your set.

296
00:26:36,040 --> 00:26:38,960
Nice music. Nice rhythm.

297
00:26:40,200 --> 00:26:44,040
I like… your beat.

298
00:26:45,320 --> 00:26:46,360
- Pete.
- Hmm?

299
00:26:47,610 --> 00:26:48,217
Well...

300
00:26:49,480 --> 00:26:50,640
Let's just be friends.

301
00:26:52,026 --> 00:26:53,026
You're not my type.

302
00:26:54,600 --> 00:26:55,600
Sorry.

303
00:26:57,840 --> 00:26:58,840
Yeah?

304
00:26:59,360 --> 00:27:00,360
Then what's your type?

305
00:27:01,200 --> 00:27:03,160
Tall, pretty, big eyes, a nepo baby?

306
00:27:09,640 --> 00:27:10,640
Guess you know it.

307
00:27:12,680 --> 00:27:13,680
Oh, yeah?

308
00:27:14,360 --> 00:27:15,760
I thought you weren't serious.

309
00:27:16,240 --> 00:27:18,920
I figured you hooked up with him
at the outing and dumped him after.

310
00:27:20,960 --> 00:27:21,960
You saw us?

311
00:27:29,560 --> 00:27:30,560
Pete,

312
00:27:31,120 --> 00:27:32,560
what exactly did you see that night?

313
00:27:35,800 --> 00:27:37,080
The faculty outing was wild.

314
00:27:39,200 --> 00:27:40,240
A lot of people hooked up.

315
00:27:47,960 --> 00:27:48,960
Was it you?

316
00:27:50,640 --> 00:27:53,440
You were the one who leaked that video
of Dean and Arnold, weren't you?

317
00:27:56,840 --> 00:27:58,160
What are you talking about, Rome?

318
00:27:59,040 --> 00:28:00,200
Why would I do that?

319
00:28:01,240 --> 00:28:03,400
I'd gain nothing from it.

320
00:28:04,360 --> 00:28:06,640
The one who benefits is Raffy.

321
00:28:07,639 --> 00:28:09,679
If they break up, it would be his turn to step in.

322
00:28:09,960 --> 00:28:13,039
Rome, why would you
settle for being his second choice?

323
00:28:13,064 --> 00:28:14,064
That's enough.

324
00:28:16,440 --> 00:28:17,800
Do you hate Raffy that much?

325
00:28:19,760 --> 00:28:23,000
If you hate him,
then stop being friends with him.

326
00:28:23,760 --> 00:28:24,760
Don't be fake.

327
00:28:26,120 --> 00:28:28,280
I feel bad for him
having someone like you as a friend.

328
00:28:46,520 --> 00:28:48,000
You sure you'll be okay living alone?

329
00:28:48,320 --> 00:28:49,720
Do you want me to move in with you?

330
00:28:50,000 --> 00:28:51,000
I'm fine.

331
00:28:51,240 --> 00:28:53,360
You're already sharing
your place with your coworker.

332
00:28:53,880 --> 00:28:55,240
But I'm worried about you.

333
00:28:59,480 --> 00:29:00,480
I'll be fine.

334
00:29:01,040 --> 00:29:02,040
It's just living alone.

335
00:29:06,760 --> 00:29:07,760
What are these?

336
00:29:09,120 --> 00:29:11,880
Things Jack and I used to share.

337
00:29:28,600 --> 00:29:32,000
These are time capsule letters.

338
00:29:34,640 --> 00:29:38,040
We used to write down things
we wanted to do each year.

339
00:29:39,040 --> 00:29:40,400
Then we'd open them the next year

340
00:29:41,040 --> 00:29:46,640
and see if we actually did them.

341
00:29:53,880 --> 00:29:56,040
You broke up.
You don't have to talk about him anymore.

342
00:29:59,120 --> 00:30:02,440
If it didn't work out,
just find someone new.

343
00:30:04,320 --> 00:30:05,600
Is it really that easy?

344
00:30:11,160 --> 00:30:12,200
I'm serious.

345
00:30:13,400 --> 00:30:15,440
I've had a realization.

346
00:30:15,640 --> 00:30:18,640
Being with someone
who doesn't love you only brings pain.

347
00:30:20,800 --> 00:30:22,000
You should love yourself.

348
00:30:23,720 --> 00:30:28,240
The other day, I dumped
my ex's stuff at this event.

349
00:30:30,200 --> 00:30:31,200
What event?

350
00:30:31,400 --> 00:30:32,400
Here.

351
00:30:33,820 --> 00:30:36,420
The Dear Ex exhibition.

352
00:30:37,046 --> 00:30:40,245
They have a spot
where you can leave your ex's things.

353
00:30:40,270 --> 00:30:42,190
Whatever isn't right, let it go.

354
00:30:50,440 --> 00:30:52,240
That's how you move on.

355
00:31:14,240 --> 00:31:16,400
Your bone isn't broken,
but you've sprained your ankle.

356
00:31:16,520 --> 00:31:21,240
From now on, avoid putting weight
on it for about one to two weeks.

357
00:31:22,840 --> 00:31:27,640
If I end up using it,
will it cause long-term problems?

358
00:31:28,160 --> 00:31:31,760
It's possible, but it's too early to tell.

359
00:31:32,320 --> 00:31:36,640
If you take proper care of it,
your body should heal on its own.

360
00:31:36,800 --> 00:31:38,040
We'll have to monitor it.

361
00:31:38,960 --> 00:31:42,800
I'll prescribe some medication
and schedule a follow-up appointment.

362
00:31:43,080 --> 00:31:44,080
Okay.

363
00:31:44,840 --> 00:31:46,640
Please wait outside.

364
00:31:47,720 --> 00:31:48,720
Thank you, doctor.

365
00:31:52,920 --> 00:31:56,200
I'VE GOT YOUR SWING DANCE
COSTUME READY. WE'RE ALL SET.

366
00:32:23,880 --> 00:32:25,080
Hey, Raffy.

367
00:32:28,280 --> 00:32:29,280
You came to class?

368
00:32:31,240 --> 00:32:32,240
Why'd you do it?

369
00:32:34,600 --> 00:32:35,600
Do what?

370
00:32:37,120 --> 00:32:38,480
You made a fake account

371
00:32:38,960 --> 00:32:40,360
and leaked Dean and Arnold's video.

372
00:32:43,160 --> 00:32:44,680
Then you let everyone think it was me.

373
00:32:48,120 --> 00:32:49,240
Not gonna say anything?

374
00:32:59,880 --> 00:33:02,119
Raffy, maybe we should take this outside.

375
00:33:02,120 --> 00:33:04,360
No. We're talking right here.

376
00:33:05,560 --> 00:33:06,560
Why'd you do it?

377
00:33:08,600 --> 00:33:10,520
Do what? I didn't do anything.

378
00:33:11,113 --> 00:33:13,473
People just assumed it was you.

379
00:33:14,240 --> 00:33:17,240
And even if I did, that's
a good thing, right?

380
00:33:17,560 --> 00:33:20,360
Call it me helping you out as a friend.

381
00:33:21,040 --> 00:33:23,320
So you could get with Jack like you wanted.

382
00:33:27,720 --> 00:33:28,720
Friend?

383
00:33:29,040 --> 00:33:31,096
What kind of fucking friend
turns the whole faculty against me?

384
00:33:31,120 --> 00:33:32,720
I don't have trash like you as a friend.

385
00:33:34,720 --> 00:33:37,240
You make up lies just
to make yourself look better.

386
00:33:39,360 --> 00:33:41,120
Like when you lied
about sleeping with Rome.

387
00:33:46,240 --> 00:33:47,240
I didn't lie.

388
00:33:47,320 --> 00:33:48,320
Oh really?

389
00:33:53,520 --> 00:33:55,280
Want to hear his dashcam recording?

390
00:33:56,440 --> 00:33:59,080
You offered to sleep with him,
and he turned you down.

391
00:34:02,400 --> 00:34:03,400
Raffy.

392
00:34:08,440 --> 00:34:12,680
And one more thing,
you embezzled the play's funds.

393
00:34:13,520 --> 00:34:14,720
Don't think it went unnoticed.

394
00:34:21,840 --> 00:34:24,280
Everyone sees you for who you are.

395
00:34:28,800 --> 00:34:31,560
You're the only one who doesn't.

396
00:34:54,520 --> 00:34:55,520
Can I have a cigarette?

397
00:35:13,240 --> 00:35:14,240
What do you want?

398
00:35:15,520 --> 00:35:16,520
You're like me.

399
00:35:17,240 --> 00:35:18,240
How am I like you?

400
00:35:19,600 --> 00:35:20,600
I'm not.

401
00:35:22,080 --> 00:35:23,320
The way you went off on Pete.

402
00:35:26,600 --> 00:35:28,040
It's the same way I went off on you.

403
00:35:28,960 --> 00:35:30,560
So what, you're here to lecture me?

404
00:35:31,400 --> 00:35:32,400
No.

405
00:35:37,999 --> 00:35:39,239
I came to apologize.

406
00:35:53,800 --> 00:35:55,120
How are things with you and Jack?

407
00:35:56,480 --> 00:35:57,480
Why do you care?

408
00:36:01,440 --> 00:36:03,080
You think I still want him?

409
00:36:05,080 --> 00:36:06,080
I just want to know.

410
00:36:08,200 --> 00:36:09,200
We broke up.

411
00:36:10,960 --> 00:36:14,400
If this were before,
I'd be glad you two broke up.

412
00:36:18,566 --> 00:36:20,006
We're going our separate ways soon.

413
00:36:21,813 --> 00:36:23,853
So let's say
we don't owe each other anything.

414
00:36:24,480 --> 00:36:26,960
You were the one cast as Romeo.

415
00:36:28,240 --> 00:36:29,240
And for Jack…

416
00:36:32,960 --> 00:36:33,960
if you ask me,

417
00:36:37,560 --> 00:36:39,240
no one can replace you.

418
00:37:00,120 --> 00:37:01,120
Tua.

419
00:37:01,160 --> 00:37:02,800
Do you think we're a bit overdressed?

420
00:37:03,760 --> 00:37:05,760
You have a costume designer boyfriend.

421
00:37:06,600 --> 00:37:09,960
I might let others win at dancing,
but not when it comes to outfits.

422
00:37:22,853 --> 00:37:23,853
Looking good.

423
00:37:24,420 --> 00:37:25,420
Let's take a selfie.

424
00:37:33,060 --> 00:37:34,216
Hello, everyone!

425
00:37:34,241 --> 00:37:40,720
Besides enjoying swing dance, we've
got a swing dance competition tonight.

426
00:37:40,920 --> 00:37:43,880
And of course,
the winners get a special prize.

427
00:37:44,080 --> 00:37:45,960
If you're ready to dance, make some noise.

428
00:37:46,360 --> 00:37:48,640
Whoo-hoo.

429
00:37:50,000 --> 00:37:50,680
Alright!

430
00:37:51,000 --> 00:37:53,079
If you're ready, gather around.

431
00:37:53,080 --> 00:37:54,359
Form a circle.

432
00:37:54,360 --> 00:37:56,240
Tua, we have to compete.

433
00:37:57,280 --> 00:37:58,280
Alright.

434
00:37:58,840 --> 00:38:01,200
But if I step on your feet,
don't be embarrassed.

435
00:38:02,440 --> 00:38:03,560
Don't worry about anything.

436
00:38:03,840 --> 00:38:09,720
Just trust me, look into my eyes,
and follow my rhythm.

437
00:38:10,640 --> 00:38:11,640
Okay?

438
00:38:12,760 --> 00:38:13,760
Let's go have some fun.

439
00:40:14,400 --> 00:40:15,599
After you leave your things behind,

440
00:40:15,600 --> 00:40:18,160
you can leave a final message to your ex
in the confession room.

441
00:40:19,480 --> 00:40:20,720
Like a confessional?

442
00:40:21,760 --> 00:40:22,760
No, not like that.

443
00:40:22,960 --> 00:40:27,040
It's a place where people can
leave one last message for their ex.

444
00:40:28,600 --> 00:40:30,680
I don't think so, but thank you.

445
00:41:26,560 --> 00:41:27,720
Why are you here alone today?

446
00:41:28,520 --> 00:41:29,880
Didn't Gameplay come with you?

447
00:41:35,320 --> 00:41:36,560
I don't live with him anymore.

448
00:41:38,560 --> 00:41:39,560
I moved out.

449
00:41:42,520 --> 00:41:44,000
I just got a new place the other day.

450
00:41:47,480 --> 00:41:51,200
I didn't do it to prove to you
I don't have feelings for him.

451
00:41:53,600 --> 00:41:54,600
I did it…

452
00:41:57,760 --> 00:41:59,640
because it's what I truly wanted.

453
00:42:05,960 --> 00:42:06,960
This necklace,

454
00:42:08,360 --> 00:42:10,160
do you really want to throw it away?

455
00:42:17,440 --> 00:42:18,440
Mm.

456
00:42:25,160 --> 00:42:26,520
I'll be honest with you, Dean.

457
00:42:27,400 --> 00:42:31,200
I gave it up because I didn't want to
break any more than I already have.

458
00:42:36,286 --> 00:42:40,846
As for these letters,
you can throw them away too.

459
00:42:44,713 --> 00:42:45,713
I'm here…

460
00:42:50,600 --> 00:42:52,160
to let them go as well.

461
00:42:56,360 --> 00:42:57,480
But the reason I came

462
00:43:02,520 --> 00:43:05,200
is to preserve the memories
we shared over those three years,

463
00:43:10,400 --> 00:43:11,400
as best as I can.

464
00:43:23,120 --> 00:43:24,120
Jack.

465
00:43:28,560 --> 00:43:30,040
Do you think we could…

466
00:43:34,400 --> 00:43:35,720
go back to being friends?

467
00:43:43,800 --> 00:43:44,800
I don't know.

468
00:43:49,720 --> 00:43:51,040
Only time will tell.

469
00:44:15,926 --> 00:44:16,966
What did you do?

470
00:44:18,240 --> 00:44:19,160
It's more swollen than

471
00:44:19,161 --> 00:44:20,240
the last time you came in.

472
00:44:23,419 --> 00:44:26,419
I went dancing.

473
00:44:27,560 --> 00:44:35,560
Didn't I tell you to avoid putting weight
on your ankle for at least one to two weeks?

474
00:44:36,400 --> 00:44:37,400
Yes, doctor.

475
00:44:38,040 --> 00:44:40,760
But I had to.

476
00:44:41,400 --> 00:44:48,760
I can't stop you, but if this continues,
your recovery will take longer.

477
00:44:49,486 --> 00:44:51,686
Your ankles support your body weight.

478
00:44:52,120 --> 00:44:57,440
If it becomes chronic,
it may not heal completely.

479
00:44:59,252 --> 00:45:02,346
So I need your cooperation.

480
00:45:03,000 --> 00:45:06,200
Avoid overusing it for the next one to
three months so it can heal properly.

481
00:45:07,680 --> 00:45:08,680
Yes, doctor.

482
00:45:19,960 --> 00:45:22,240
Didn't you think to tell me
your ankle was hurting?

483
00:45:22,920 --> 00:45:25,016
Don't tell me it's been like this
since the accident at the park.

484
00:45:25,040 --> 00:45:26,840
What was I supposed to do, Tua?

485
00:45:27,120 --> 00:45:29,720
You really wanted to go to Swing Night.

486
00:45:30,360 --> 00:45:31,800
And I gave you my word.

487
00:45:32,320 --> 00:45:33,480
Your word?

488
00:45:34,040 --> 00:45:35,040
This is serious.

489
00:45:36,840 --> 00:45:40,680
What could I have done?
I keep my promises.

490
00:45:46,560 --> 00:45:48,280
And what if it turns into a chronic injury?

491
00:45:48,880 --> 00:45:50,519
You need to take better care of yourself.

492
00:45:50,520 --> 00:45:52,000
Come on, Tua.

493
00:45:53,040 --> 00:45:56,040
I'll recover faster if you take care of me.

494
00:45:58,819 --> 00:45:59,819
Yeah?

495
00:46:00,840 --> 00:46:01,840
Or what?

496
00:46:02,600 --> 00:46:04,040
You're not going to take care of me?

497
00:46:04,373 --> 00:46:07,055
Look, I can barely walk.

498
00:46:07,080 --> 00:46:08,680
I can't get around properly.

499
00:46:09,400 --> 00:46:10,720
And I live alone.

500
00:46:12,000 --> 00:46:13,560
Can I stay at your place?

501
00:46:15,320 --> 00:46:16,320
Please.

502
00:46:17,480 --> 00:46:19,068
Please, please.

503
00:46:22,000 --> 00:46:23,000
Okay.

504
00:46:23,240 --> 00:46:24,240
That's my boy.

505
00:46:41,600 --> 00:46:42,600
Hey.

506
00:46:43,200 --> 00:46:45,480
A friend of a friend was looking for a DJ.

507
00:46:45,880 --> 00:46:47,040
So I gave them your contact.

508
00:46:47,520 --> 00:46:48,520
Oh?

509
00:46:48,800 --> 00:46:50,040
So you're managing my gigs now?

510
00:46:50,720 --> 00:46:52,280
What? You don't want the job?

511
00:46:54,080 --> 00:46:55,080
I do.

512
00:46:55,360 --> 00:46:56,360
I take any gig.

513
00:47:00,040 --> 00:47:01,880
So when are you making me a new playlist?

514
00:47:02,520 --> 00:47:03,920
To replace the one you deleted.

515
00:47:04,680 --> 00:47:06,400
You can just listen to some other channels.

516
00:47:07,560 --> 00:47:08,560
Come on.

517
00:47:10,560 --> 00:47:12,480
I want my old playlist back.

518
00:47:13,000 --> 00:47:15,320
I've got nothing to listen
to right now. Please.

519
00:47:17,480 --> 00:47:18,480
Not yet.

520
00:47:18,640 --> 00:47:19,640
I'm not inspired yet.

521
00:47:20,280 --> 00:47:22,280
And when will you be?

522
00:47:24,280 --> 00:47:25,760
When I'm in the mood.

523
00:47:26,640 --> 00:47:27,640
That's when.

524
00:47:28,240 --> 00:47:29,800
In the mood?

525
00:47:33,687 --> 00:47:36,073
Mm…

526
00:48:18,560 --> 00:48:19,560
Then…

527
00:48:21,520 --> 00:48:23,440
Let me change your playlist title first.

528
00:48:32,800 --> 00:48:36,840
Take out “not”
and leave “I'm your backup plan.”

529
00:48:51,413 --> 00:48:52,413
Ready?

530
00:48:53,320 --> 00:48:54,320
Yeah.

531
00:48:54,413 --> 00:48:55,413
I'm ready.

532
00:48:57,440 --> 00:48:58,880
Just focus on your camera work.

533
00:49:09,320 --> 00:49:11,560
I never thought
I'd ever say something like this.

534
00:49:13,440 --> 00:49:15,680
If this were the last time
I could say anything to you…

535
00:49:17,480 --> 00:49:18,760
I'd want you to know

536
00:49:20,280 --> 00:49:21,320
I loved you so much.

537
00:49:22,920 --> 00:49:27,240
Thank you for staying by my side
when I had no one left.

538
00:49:28,720 --> 00:49:31,320
Thank you for holding me on my worst days.

539
00:49:32,720 --> 00:49:35,000
Because of you,
I learned how to love myself more.

540
00:49:36,600 --> 00:49:41,560
I always believed there was a way
through everything because I had you.

541
00:49:42,360 --> 00:49:47,360
And even though I don't have you anymore,
I'm still grateful.

542
00:49:48,920 --> 00:49:51,760
You were the best love
that ever happened to me.

543
00:50:10,360 --> 00:50:11,360
Jack.

544
00:50:15,920 --> 00:50:17,480
Do you remember what you told me?

545
00:50:19,280 --> 00:50:20,280
You said I had no layers.

546
00:50:23,160 --> 00:50:26,760
I said what I felt. I did what I felt.

547
00:50:28,240 --> 00:50:29,640
Because I was sensitive.

548
00:50:33,760 --> 00:50:35,600
Because I was honest with my feelings.

549
00:50:39,279 --> 00:50:40,279
I used to argue with you.

550
00:50:41,040 --> 00:50:42,040
I thought you were wrong.

551
00:50:43,800 --> 00:50:49,240
I thought I could act
just as well in real life as I do on stage.

552
00:50:53,360 --> 00:50:54,920
But, in fact, I can't.

553
00:51:15,320 --> 00:51:17,640
I can't act like I'm not
hurting because of you.

554
00:51:24,000 --> 00:51:25,200
I'm heartbroken.

555
00:51:56,800 --> 00:51:58,520
I can't act like I don't care about you.

556
00:52:05,600 --> 00:52:07,120
I can't even be friends with you.

557
00:52:14,840 --> 00:52:16,120
I can't be your friend.

558
00:52:24,520 --> 00:52:25,960
You're my dream.

559
00:52:28,000 --> 00:52:32,720
You're the only person in this world
who sees my worth.

560
00:52:35,840 --> 00:52:40,440
You once said I was your number one actor.

561
00:52:49,360 --> 00:52:51,280
You were my number one too.

562
00:53:28,360 --> 00:53:29,360
Jack.

563
00:53:37,880 --> 00:53:39,120
- I…
- Say no more.

564
00:53:58,700 --> 00:53:59,820
I forgive you.

565
00:55:03,360 --> 00:55:04,680
(Next Episode)
Time really flies.

566
00:55:04,880 --> 00:55:06,840
Before we knew it,
we're graduating already.

567
00:55:07,480 --> 00:55:10,840
Thank you so much, Rome,
for seeing my worth.

568
00:55:12,760 --> 00:55:13,760
Will you be my boyfriend?

569
00:55:14,760 --> 00:55:18,200
Have you considered living
with me over there after graduation?

570
00:55:21,120 --> 00:55:22,400
My dream is here too.

571
00:55:22,800 --> 00:55:24,280
I still want to stay and work here.

572
00:55:24,480 --> 00:55:26,759
I'm going to fight
as hard as I can for a future here.

573
00:55:26,760 --> 00:55:29,000
From now on, I'll fight for you too.

574
00:55:29,025 --> 00:55:32,098
Getting to meet you was worth it.

575
00:55:32,646 --> 00:55:35,726
You and I are
parting ways to live our own lives.
